<!--Game Overview-->

    <section id="overview">
        <h2>Game Overview</h2>
        <p>Chess is a two-player strategy board game that has been around for centuries. The objective is to checkmate the opponent's king. The game is played on an 8x8 grid with 16 pieces per player, including pawns, knights, bishops, rooks, a queen, and a king.</p>
        <p>The game originated in India in the 6th century and spread to Persia and then Europe. Today, it is played worldwide, with official tournaments and championships held regularly.</p>
    </section>

